item.title: [CRYPTO-137] Error compiling on Win64 with Mingw
item.description:
Followed steps in "BUILDING.txt" on Windows 10 64-bit but cannot compile native due to inline errors. I see a "Fixed" issue https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CRYPTO-116 with similar issue, and flag is included in GCC step but does not fix errors.

Below is the GCC log, and the full log for mvn clean test with "-d" flag.

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
Try commenting out line 137 of  file org_apache_commons_crypto.h

#define inline __inline;

Got me past the inline errors but the current master branch Windows build is further broken because of the merge with the 1.1 support branch.  I'm working that now and I'll submit a PR for review and discussion once I get it working.  I'd like to get another release out per CRYPTO-143.

Using the minGW 64 bit compiler.
Fixed by aremily but can't assign the bug to him.
